%20flares%20from%20a%20position%20directly%20over%20an%20MQ-9%20drone%20on%20a%20defeat-ISIS%20mission%20in%20Syria%20July%2023%2C%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c2e037cf0778001965e56d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22605%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20fighter%20flies%20dangerously%20close%20to%20a%20US%20MQ-9%20before%20deploying%20flares%20from%20a%20position%20directly%20over%20an%20MQ-9%20drone%20on%20a%20defeat-ISIS%20mission%20in%20Syria%20July%2023%2C%202023%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussian%20fighter%20jets%20have%20harassed%20US%20military%20drones%20on%20numerous%20occasions%20throughout%20July.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20recent%20provocation%2C%20Moscow's%20pilots%20dropped%20flares%20that%20damaged%20an%20MQ-9%20Reaper%20drone.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EExperts%20say%20the%20recent%20provocations%20are%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20Kremlin%20boast%20its%20military%20power%20where%20it%20can.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20fighter%20jets%20have%20harassed%20and%20bullied%20US%20military%20drones%20operating%20above%20Syria%20routinely%20throughout%20July%2C%20with%20one%20engagement%20this%20week%20actually%20damaging%20an%20American%20aircraft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20are%20frustrated%20with%20the%20repeated%20incidents%2C%20blasting%20Moscow's%20pilots%20for%20dangerous%20and%20reckless%20behavior%2C%20and%20accusing%20Russia%20of%20interfering%20with%20combat%20drones%20on%20high-profile%20counterterrorism%20missions.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EExperts%20say%20there%20are%20several%20reasons%20behind%20the%20spike%20in%20aggressive%20behavior%2C%20including%20Russian%20overcompensation%20for%20its%20military%20shortcomings%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20a%20desire%20to%20flex%20its%20muscles%20in%20an%20area%20where%20it%20still%20enjoys%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20sees%20its%20activities%20in%20Syria%20%26quot%3Bas%20one%20area%20that%20really%20speaks%20to%20Russian%20global%20power%20and%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20Lokker%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20Russian%20foreign%20policy%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%20(CNAS)%2C%20told%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20Moscow%20is%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Breally%20shape%20international%20affairs%20according%20to%20its%20own%20interests%26quot%3B%20there.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20maintain%20a%20military%20presence%20in%20Syria.%20Washington%20has%20around%20900%20troops%20deployed%20for%20counterterrorism%20operations%20against%20the%20Islamic%20State%20while%20Moscow%20helps%20support%20the%20country's%20brutal%20regime%20in%20its%20ongoing%20civil%20war.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20largely%20managed%20to%20avoid%20clashes%20there%20even%20as%20they%20pursued%20their%20respective%20interests.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bilateral%20relationship%20between%20Washington%20and%20Moscow%20hit%20rock%20bottom%20after%20the%20latter's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022.%20It%20hasn't%20improved%20in%20the%2017%20months%20since%2C%20and%20the%20relationship%20isn't%20showing%20any%20signs%20of%20reconciliation%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20Recent%20engagements%20in%20the%20skies%20above%20Syria%20have%20only%20elevated%20tensions%20between%20the%20two%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20a%20Russian%20Su-35%20fighter%20jet%20flew%20within%20several%20meters%20of%20a%20US%20MQ-9%20Reaper%20drone%20on%20a%20counterterrorism%20mission%20and%20deployed%20flares%20above%20the%20American%20aircraft.%20One%20of%20the%20flares%20hit%20the%20drone%20and%20damaged%20its%20propeller%2C%20although%20the%20crew%20remotely%20piloting%20the%20MQ-9%20managed%20to%20safely%20bring%20it%20back%20to%20base.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Damage%20to%20the%20Reaper%20drone's%20propeller.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bfd682ed4f460019630624%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDamage%20to%20the%20Reaper%20drone's%20propeller.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Russian%20fighter's%20blatant%20disregard%20for%20flight%20safety%20detracts%20from%20our%20mission%20to%20ensure%20the%20enduring%20defeat%20of%20ISIS%2C%26quot%3B%20Lt.%20Gen.%20Alexus%20Grynkewich%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20US%20Air%20Forces%20Central%20Command%20(AFCENT)%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20call%20upon%20the%20Russian%20forces%20in%20Syria%20to%20put%20an%20immediate%20end%20to%20this%20reckless%2C%20unprovoked%2C%20and%20unprofessional%20behavior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20incident%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20demonstrations%20of%20Russian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-jets-bully-us-reaper-drones-syria-afterburners-flares-video-2023-7%5C%22%3Eaggression%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20US%20military%20drones%20this%20month.%20The%20first%20week%20of%20July%20featured%20three%20straight%20days%20of%20provocations%20by%20Moscow's%20pilots%2C%20who%20harassed%20multiple%20American%20MQ-9%20Reaper%20drones%20by%20engaging%20afterburners%2C%20dropping%20parachute%20flares%2C%20and%20flying%20in%20close%20proximity%20to%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20one%20of%20these%20engagements%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-criticizes-russia-after-it-harassed-us-drones-targeting-isis-2023-7%5C%22%3Ejeopardized%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20counterterrorism%20mission.%20On%20July%207%2C%20Russian%20fighter%20jets%20flew%2018%20close%20passes%20near%20several%20Reaper%20drones%20during%20an%20encounter%20that%20lasted%20nearly%20two%20hours%20and%20was%20described%20by%20a%20U