n%20following%20their%20talks%20at%20the%20Kremlin%20in%20Moscow%20on%20March%2021%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EPAVEL%20BYRKIN%2FSPUTNIK%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussian%20imports%20of%20Chinese%20cars%20rocketed%20543%25%20in%20the%20first%20half%2C%20local%20media%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussia%20now%20gets%2070%25%20of%20its%20imported%20cars%20from%20China%2C%20compared%20with%20just%2010%25%20prior%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat%20highlights%20Russia's%20growing%20economic%20dependency%20on%20China%20%E2%80%93%20thanks%20to%20Moscow's%20deepening%20from%20the%20West.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20deepening%20economic%20and%20political%20isolation%20from%20the%20West%20is%20dramatically%20reshaping%20its%20business%20and%20consumer%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20theme%20to%20emerge%20amid%20Moscow's%20struggles%20with%20Western%20sanctions%2C%20slapped%20in%20response%20to%20its%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20is%20probably%20the%20Eurasian%20nation's%20growing%20economic%20dependency%20on%20China%20%E2%80%93%20for%20everything%20from%20selling%20oil%20to%20buying%20consumer%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20now%20the%20world's%20No.%201%20buyer%20of%20Chinese%20cars%2C%20after%20western%20manufacturers%20such%20as%20General%20Motors%2C%20Ford%2C%20and%20Mercedes-Benz%20exited%20the%20country%20in%20response%20to%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20figures%20for%20Russia's%202023%20automobile%20imports%20from%20China%20are%20striking.%20Inbound%20shipments%20of%20Chinese%20cars%20saw%20a%20stunning%20543%25%20surge%20in%20the%20first%20half%20to%20%244.6%20billion%20in%20value%2C%20from%20the%20same%20period%20of%202022%2C%20the%20Russian%20news%20website%20RBC%20reported%20this%20week%2C%20citing%20figures%20from%20the%20Chinese%20customs%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20Chinese%20cars%20made%20up%20just%2010%25%