%2Fglobal%2Fcineworld-250-million-credit-facility-1235682112%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%2C%20Japanese%20Scientists%20Find%20600-Million-Year-Old%20Ocean%20In%20Himalayas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHigh%20up%20in%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20scientists%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20(IISc)%20and%20Niigata%20University%2C%20Japan%2C%20have%20discovered%20droplets%20of%20water%20trapped%20in%20mineral%20deposits%20that%20were%20likely%20left%20behind%20from%20an%20ancient%20ocean%20which%20existed%20around%20600%20million%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysis%20of%20the%20deposits%2C%20which%20had%20both%20calcium%20and%20magnesium%20carbonates%2C%20also%20allowed%20the%20team%20to%20provide%20a%20possible%20explanation%20for%20events%20that%20might%20have%20led%20to%20a%20major%20oxygenation%20event%20in%20Earth's%20history%2C%20Bengaluru-based%20IISc%20said%20in%20a%20release%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20found%20a%20time%20capsule%20for%20paleo%20oceans%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Prakash%20Chandra%20Arya%2C%20PhD%20student%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Earth%20Sciences%20(CEaS)%2C%20IISc%2C%20and%20first%20author%20of%20the%20study%20published%20in%20'Precambrian%20Research'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20statement%2C%20scientists%20believe%20that%20between%20700%20and%20500%20million%20years%20ago%2C%20thick%20sheets%20of%20ice%20covered%20the%20Earth%20for%20an%20extended%20period%2C%20called%20the%20Snowball%20Earth%20glaciation%20(one%20of%20the%20major%20glacial%20events%20in%20Earth's%20history).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20followed%20this%2C%20it%20said%2C%20was%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20oxygen%20in%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20called%20the%20Second%20Great%20Oxygenation%20Event%2C%20which%20eventually%20led%20to%20the%20evolution%20of%20complex%20life%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20scientists%20have%20not%20fully%20understood%20how%20these%20events%20were%20connected%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20well-preserved%20fossils%20and%20the%20disappearance%20of%20all%20past%20oceans%20that%20existed%20in%20the%20Earth's%20history%2C%20IISc%20noted%2C%20adding%20that%20exposures%20of%20such%20marine%20rocks%20in%20the%20Himalayas%20can%20provide%20some%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20much%20about%20past%20oceans%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Arya.%20%26quot%3BHow%20different%20or%20similar%20were%20they%20compared%20to%20present-day%20oceans%3F%20Were%20they%20more%20acidic%20or%20basic%2C%20nutrient-rich%20or%20deficient%2C%20warm%20or%20cold%2C%20and%20what%20was%20their%20chemical%20and%20isotopic%20composition%3F%26quot%3B%20Such%20insights%20could%20also%20provide%20clues%20about%20the%20Earth's%20past%20climate%2C%20and%20this%20information%20can%20be%20useful%20for%20climate%20modelling%2C%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deposits%20found%20by%20the%20team%20-%20which%20date%20back%20to%20around%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Snowball%20Earth%20glaciation%20-%20showed%20that%20the%20sedimentary%20basins%20were%20deprived%20of%20calcium%20for%20an%20extended%20period%2C%20probably%20due%20to%20low%20riverine%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20this%20time%2C%20there%20was%20no%20flow%20in%20the%20oceans%2C%20and%20hence%20no%20calcium%20input.%20When%20there%20is%20no%20flow%20or%20calcium%20input%2C%20as%20more%20calcium%20precipitates%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20magnesium%20goes%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Sajeev%20Krishnan%2C%20Professor%20at%20CEaS%20and%20corresponding%20author%20of%20the%20study.%20The%20magnesium%20deposits%20formed%20at%20this%20time%20were%20able%20to%20trap%20paleo%20ocean%20water%20in%20their%20pore%20space%20as%20they%20crystallised%2C%20the%20researchers%20suggest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20calcium%20deprivation%20also%20likely%20led%20to%20a%20nutrient%20deficiency%2C%20making%20it%20conducive%20for%20slow-growing%20photosynthetic%20cyanobacteria%2C%20which%20could%20have%20started%20spewing%20out%20more%20oxygen%20into%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhenever%20there%20is%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20oxygen%20level%20in%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20you%20will%20have%20biological%20radiation%20(evolution)%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Arya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20hunted%20for%20these%20deposits%20across%20a%20long%20stretch%20of%20the%20western%20Kumaon%20Himalayas%2C%20extending%20from%20Amritpur%20to%20the%20Milam%20glacier%2C%20and%20Dehradun%20to%20the%20Gangotri%20glacier%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20extensive%20laboratory%20analysis%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20confirm%20that%20the%20deposits%20are%20a%20product%20of%20precipitation%20from%20ancient%20ocean%20water%2C%20and%20not%20from%20other%20places%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Earth's%20interior%20(for%20example%2C%20from%20submarine%20volcanic%20activity).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20believe%20that%20these%20deposits%20can%20provide%20information%20about%20ancient%20oceanic%20conditions%20such%20as%20pH%2C%20chemistry%2C%20and%20isotopic%20composition%2C%20which%20have%20so%20far%20only%20been%20theorised%20or%20modelled.%20Such%20information%20can%20help%20answer%20questions%20related%20to%20the%20evolution%20of%20oceans%2C%20and%20even%20life%2C%20in%20Earth's%20history%2C%20it%20was%20stated.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690528260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Frc9kjpkc_himalayas-generic-himalayan-range-trek-generic-pixabay_625x300_28_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-japanese-scientists-discover-600-million-year-old-ocean-water-in-himalayas-4247608%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22High%20in%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20scientists%20f