es%20wanted%20to%20set%20up%20in%20Telangana.%20He%20had%20reached%20out%20to%20Bolivia%E2%80%99s%20ambassadors%20in%20India.%20Travelling%20to%20the%20country%2C%20he%20had%20met%20senior%20executives%20at%20state-owned%20mining%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ylb.gob.bo%2F%5C%22%3EYacimientos%20de%20Litio%20Bolivianos%3C%2Fa%3E%20(YLB).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20even%20brought%20a%20delegation%20of%20Bolivian%20officials%20to%20India%E2%80%94to%20get%20them%20to%20meet%20the%20state%20government%2C%20research%20bodies%20like%20state-owned%20ARCI%20(International%20Advanced%20Research%20Centre%20for%20Powder%20Metallurgy%20and%20New%20Materials)%20and%20EV%20industry%20executives.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20was%20in%202019%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sunkavalli%20told%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20then%2C%20there%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnacla.org%2Freview-coup-story-violence-and-resistance-bolivia%5C%22%3Ecoup%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Bolivia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvo%20Morales%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2F2019_Bolivian_political_crisis%5C%22%3Eoverthrown%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20weeks%20that%20followed%2C%20the%20former%20president%20would%20call%20the%20coup%20an%20American%20attempt%20to%20stop%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2019%2F12%2F25%2Fmorales-claims-us-orchestrated-coup-to-tap-bolivias-lithium%5C%22%3EBolivia%E2%80%99s%20lithium%20extraction%20partnerships%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20China%20and%20Russia.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20as%20collateral%20damage%2C%20Sunkavalli%E2%80%99s%20plans%20seemed%20imperilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20not%20only%20did%20the%20company%20turn%20to%20other%20Latin%20American%20sources%2C%20including%20Brazil%2C%20it%20also%20approached%20the%20Telangana%20government.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20met%20KT%20Rama%20Rao%2C%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20industries%20minister%2C%20and%20told%20him%20about%20our%20plans%20to%20source%20lithium%20from%20Bolivia.%E2%80%9D%20After%20that%2C%20Telangana%20State%20Mining%20and%20Development%20Corporation%20(TSMDC)%20got%20involved%20in%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20talks%20with%20Bolivia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELand-locked%20Telangana%2C%20with%20little%20mineral%20resources%20of%20its%20own%2C%20is%20trying%20to%20groom%20itself%20into%20a%20manufacturing%20cluster%20for%20emerging%20sectors%20like%20data%20centres%2C%20medical%20devices%2C%20aerospace%20and%20life%20sciences.%20EVs%20and%20EV%20components%20are%20in%20that%20list%20as%20well%E2%80%94in%202019%2C%20it%20announced%20plans%20to%20set%20up%20a%20multi-gigawatt%20lithium%20battery%20manufacturing%20cluster.%20To%20differentiate%20itself%20from%20other%20states%20wooing%20the%20EV%20supply%20chain%2C%20said%20Sunkavalli%2C%20the%20state%20also%20told%20TSMDC%20in%202020%20to%20acquire%20mines%20and%20minerals%20needed%20for%20cell%20manufacturing.%20Its%20rationale%3F%20Securing%20critical%20mineral%20supplies%20would%20give%20it%20a%20competitive%20advantage%20over%20other%20geographies%20vying%20to%20attract%20the%20EV%20value%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKABIL%20(Khanij%20Bidesh%20India%20Ltd)%20has%20similar%20compulsions.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Fdigging-into-indias-critical-minerals-dash%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20part%20of%20this%20series%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%2C%20India%20might%20need%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fpti-stories%2Findia-s-battery-storage-potential-to-be-600-gwh-by-2030-niti-report-122072200618_1.html%5C%22%3E600%20GWH%20of%20battery%20storage%20by%202030%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20make%20all%20of%20these%20locally%2C%20the%20country%20will%20need%20600%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20lithium.%20%E2%80%9COne%20GWh%20of%20Cathode%20Active%20Material%20(CAM)%20will%20need%20about%201%2C000%20MT%20of%20Lithium%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sunkavalli%20told%20CarbonCopy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20procure%20such%20volumes%2C%20not%20only%20is%20KABIL%20trying%20to%20pick%20up%20minority%20stakes%20in%20critical%20mineral%20mines%2C%20it%20is%20also%20extending%20governmental%20support%20to%20private%20companies%20forging%20deals.%20%E2%80%9C(KABIL)%20says%20%3Cu%3Ecompanies%20should%20go%2C%20identify%20potential%20mines%2C%20and%20then%20it%20will%20support%20and%20secure%20(supplies)%20via%20a%20G2G%20deal%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kiriti%20Varma%2C%20a%20co-founder%20of%20Altmin.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20when%20CarbonCopy%20spoke%20to%20Sunkavalli%2C%20he%20said%20discussions%20with%20YLB%20were%20back%20on%20track%20after%20the%20coup%20failed%E2%80%94and%20a%20democratic%20government%20returned%20to%20power.%20The%20company%20is%20now%20readying%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fallox-to-set-up-750-cr-c-lfp-battery-material-unit-in-telangana%2Farticle66386044.ece%5C%22%3E3%20GWh%20CAM%20(Cathode%20Active%20Material)%20manufacturing%20plant%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHardwired%20into%20Altmin%E2%80%99s%20experience%20is%20a%20larger%20story.%20As%20countries%20vie%20to%20secure%20their%20critical%20mineral%20supplies%2C%20how%20is%20India%2C%20as%20a%20relatively%20industrialised%20developing%20country%2C%20navigating%20this%20competition%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%8B%3Cstrong%3EThe%20question%20about%20geopolitics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOurs%20is%20a%20time%20when%20global%20critical%20mineral%20supply%20chains%20are%20in%20turmoil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20hand%2C%20like%20India%2C%20nations%20without%20critical%20mineral%20deposits%20are%20trying%20to%20secure%20independent%20supplies%20of%20these%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EU%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eiu.com%2Fn%2Feu-acts-to-secure-access-to-critical-raw-materials%2F%5C%22%3ECritical%20Minerals%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20seeks%20to%20secure%20its%20supplies%20of%20critical%20minerals.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.txfnews.com%2Farticles%2F7425%2Fmore-countries-pursue-security-of-supply-of-critical-minerals%5C%22%3ECanada%2C%20Australia%20and%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20similar%20legislations.%20Wanting%20to%20phase%20China%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fbf026121-7d97-47d9-8729-a6f78779c40e%5C%22%3Eits%20battery%20supply%20chain%20by%20the%20beginning%20of%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20USA%20has%20launched%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fminerals-security-partnership-what-is-it-and-why-is-it-important-123062200413_1.html%5C%22%3EMinerals%20Security%20Partnership%3C%2Fa%3E%20(MSP)%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20nine%20other%20partner%20countries.%20It%E2%80%99s%20this%20coalition%20that%20India%20has%20newly%20entered.%20(Companies%20are%20getting%20into%20this%20race%20as%20well.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestorintel.com%2Fcritical-minerals-rare-earths%2Fdoes-nationalization-loom-for-critical-minerals%2F%5C%22%3EGM%20and%20Mercedes%20Benz%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20invested%20in%20lithium%20producers.%20Tesla%2C%20too%2C%20is%20backwards%20integrating%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergy.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpower%2Felon-musk-and-tesla-break-ground-on-massive-texas-lithium-refinery%2F100094830%5C%22%3Elithium%20refining%20and%20processing%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20trend%20of%20friend-shoring%E2%80%94where%20countries%20are%20vying%20to%20secure%20critical%20mineral%20supplies%20for%20them%20and%20their%20allies%E2%80%94is%20counterbalanced%20by%20a%20parallel%20trend%20of%20resource%20nationalism.%20One%20set%20of%20countries%E2%80%94like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestorintel.com%2Fcritical-minerals-rare-earths%2Fdoes-nationalization-loom-for-critical-minerals%2F%5C%22%3EPeru%2C%20Argentina%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Congo%20and%20Kazakhstan%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94are%20nationalising%20their%20critical%20mineral%20reserves%20to%20have%20greater%20say%20on%20realisations%20from%20ore%20exports.%20Another%20set%20no%20longer%20wants%20to%20export%20raw%20ore.%20In%202020%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20home%20to%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20nickel%20reserves%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Finvestments-indonesias-nickel-industry-2023-02-06%2F%5C%22%3Ebanned%20exports%20of%20unprocessed%20nickel%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20miners%20to%20process%20the%20ore%20locally%E2%80%94albeit%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2Finteractive%2F2023%2Fev-nickel-refinery-dangers%2F%5C%22%3Ehigh%20environmental%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%E2%80%99s%20now%20getting%20companies%20to%20build%20production%20capacities%20along%20the%20EV%20supply%20chain%E2%80%94from%20plants%20that%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Finvestments-indonesias-nickel-industry-2023-02-06%2F%5C%22%3EEV%20battery%20materials%3B%20to%20battery%20cell%20plants%3B%20and%20EVs%20themselves%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20only%20one.%20Australia%2C%20which%20used%20to%20export%20lithium%20to%20China%20for%20processing%20wants%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ffuture%2Farticle%2F20221110-how-australia-became-the-worlds-greatest-lithium-supplier%5C%22%3Eprocess%20ore%20locally%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20do%20countries%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining-technology.com%2Ffeatures%2Fzimbabwe-critical-minerals-resource-nationalism%2F%5C%22%3EZimbabwe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining.com%2Fmexico-passes-mining-reform-nationalizing-lithium%2F%5C%22%3EMexico%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fchile-lithium-industry-state-control-boric-36aa76e08f211579e17f2df386143b9a%5C%22%3EChile%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining.com%2Fweb%2Fafrica-gears-up-to-keep-more-of-the-profits-from-lithium-boom%2F%5C%22%3ENamibia%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos-transportation%2Fchina-automaker-byd-invest-620-million-brazil-industrial-complex-2023-07-04%2F%5C%22%3EBrazil%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outcome%3F%20To%20lock%20mineral-rich%20countries%20into%20long-term%20supply%20contracts%2C%20buyers%20will%20have%20to%20locate%20a%20part%20of%20their%20value%20chains%20in%20these%20countries%E2%80%94which%2C%20however%2C%20creates%20a%20precondition%20for%20expertise%20in%20refining%20and%20technological%2Fmanufacturing%20competitiveness%E2%80%94areas%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Findia-s-first-critical-mineral-list-a-road-towards-supply-chain-security-123062900547_1.html%5C%22%3EIndia%20is%20weak%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20others%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fhow-china-came-to-dominate-the-worlds-largest-nickel-source-for-electric-cars-4c081a12%5C%22%3EChina%20are%20strong%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompetition%20is%20similarly%20underway%20to%20lure%20green%20manufacturing%20chains.%20The%20USA%20has%20launched%20legislation%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Findustries%2Fpublic-sector%2Four-insights%2Fthe-inflation-reduction-act-heres-whats-in-it%5C%22%3EInflation%20Reduction%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IRA)%20which%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20wants%20to%20boost%20clean%20energy%20manufacturing%20in%20the%20country.%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fbf026121-7d97-47d9-8729-a6f78779c40e%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20US%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20offers%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20tax%20credits%20to%20battery%20companies%20only%20if%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20the%20value%20of%20critical%20minerals%20contained%20in%20their%20products%20is%20processed%20or%20extracted%20in%20the%20US%20or%20by%20partners%20with%20free%20trade%20agreements.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outcome%20is%20heightened%20competition%20for%20not%20just%20mineral%20reserves%2C%20but%20also%20manufacturing%20units.%20The%20IRA%20is%20showing%20results.%20Even%20Indian%20companies%E2%80%94like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fgroup-backed-by-indias-vikram-solar-invest-15-billion-new-us-factories-2023-06-22%2F%5C%22%3EVikram%20Solar%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fepsilon-to-establish-ev-battery-component-factory-in-us-sets-aside-650-mn-123062600300_1.html%5C%22%3EEpsilon%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94are%20setting%20up%20manufacturing%20units%20in%20the%20USA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20this%2C%20China%20is%20not%20sitting%20idle%20either.%20Not%20only%20is%20it%20setting%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FSpotlight%2FCaixin%2FChina-s-hunt-for-strategic-new-energy-minerals%5C%22%3Eprocessing%20and%20battery%20plants%20in%20countries%20that%20have%20nationalised%20their%20deposits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20lead%20in%20R%26amp%3BD.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20most%20batteries%20have%20an%20energy%20density%20below%20300%20watt%20hours%2Fkilogram%2C%20CATL%20has%20just%20unveiled%20a%20battery%20capable%20of%20storing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2Fscience%2F2023-05-03%2Fcatl-announces-battery-to-make-electric-aviation-possible%2F102289310%5C%22%3E500%20wh%2Fkg%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%E2%80%99s%20expected%20to%20find%20use%20in%20aviation%20as%20well%20as%20boost%20EVs%E2%80%99%20range%20to%201%2C000%20km%20per%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20response%20to%20this%2C%20countries%20and%20companies%20are%20trying%20to%20pare%20their%20critical%20mineral%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20ongoing%20centrality%20of%20lithium%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20at%20the%20most%20superficial%20level%2C%20battery%20technology%20is%20fascinating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECells%20have%20a%20cathode%2C%20an%20anode%2C%20a%20separator%20and%20an%20electrolyte.%20Anode%2C%20usually%20made%20of%20graphite%2C%20is%20weak%20at%20retaining%20electrons.%20Cathode%20(or%20CAM%2C%20Cathode%20Active%20Material%20comprising%20a%20mix%20of%20minerals%20including%20lithium)%20exerts%20a%20stronger%20pull%20on%20electrons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20battery%20is%20charging%2C%20lithium%20ions%20move%20through%20the%20separator%2Felectrolyte%20to%20the%20anode.%20When%20discharging%2C%20they%20move%20back%20to%20the%20cathode.%20As%20the%20cathode%20becomes%20more%20positively%20charged%20than%20the%20anode%2C%20negatively-charged%20electrons%20follow%20them.%20The%20separator%2C%20however%2C%20blocks%20their%20flow%20through%20the%20battery%E2%80%94making%20them%20flow%20%3Cem%3Ethrough%20the%20device%20being%20powered%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20the%20cathode.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20anode%20and%20cathode%20come%20in%20diverse%20configurations%E2%80%94each%20with%20its%20own%20characteristics.%20Lithium%20Titanate%20(LTO)%20can%20be%20used%20as%20anode%20instead%20of%20graphite.%20Those%20cells%20charge%20faster%2C%20but%20have%20lower%20energy%20density%2C%20said%20Uttam%20Sen%2C%20co-founder%20of%20e-TRNL%20Energy%2C%20a%20Bangalore-based%20cell-manufacturing%20startup%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECAMs%2C%20too%2C%20come%20in%20diverse%20forms.%20NMC%20(Nickel%20Manganese%20Cobalt%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20combined%20with%20lithium)%20and%20LFP%20(Lithium%20Iron%20Phosphate)%20dominate%20the%20world%20right%20now.%20CAMs%20are%20also%20made%20from%20LTO%20(Lithium%20Titanium%20Oxide)%2C%20LMO%20(Lithium%20Ion%20Manganese%20Oxide)%2C%20NCA%20(Lithium%20Nickel%20Cobalt%20and%20Aluminum%20Oxide)%2C%20and%20LMNO%20(Lithium%20Manganese%20Nickel%20Oxide).%20While%20each%20comes%20with%20different%20qualities%E2%80%94nickel%20adds%20capacity%2C%20manganese%20and%20cobalt%20lend%20stability%2C%20aluminium%20increases%20power%2C%20says%20this%20page%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsungsdi.com%2F%2520column%2Ftechnology%2Fdetail%2F56458.html%5C%22%3ESamsung%3C%2Fa%3E%20website%E2%80%94lithium%20is%20a%20common%20element%20in%20all%20of%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20morning%20in%20April%2C%20trying%20to%20understand%20why%2C%20CarbonCopy%20met%20Sagar%20Mitra.%20A%20professor%20at%20IIT%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Department%20of%20Energy%20Science%20and%20Engineering%3B%20he%20has%20been%20working%20on%20lithium%20from%20the%20days%20of%20his%20PhD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20EV%20makes%20three%20demands%20on%20its%20batteries%2C%20Mitra%20said%20that%20day.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20needs%20batteries%20that%20can%20produce%20the%20high%20output%20needed%20to%20get%20a%20stationary%20vehicle%20moving%20without%20discharging%20completely.%E2%80%9D%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20should%20recharge%20quickly%20and%20not%20be%20too%20heavy.%20Given%20the%20relative%20ease%20with%20which%20it%20sheds%20electrons%2C%20lithium-based%20batteries%20have%20the%20highest%20energy%20density%20of%20any%20battery%20technology%20today.%20In%20addition%2C%20lithium-based%20cells%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cei.washington.edu%2Feducation%2Fscience-of-solar%2Fbattery-technology%2F%5C%22%3Edeliver%20up%20to%203.6%20volts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20other%20chemistries%20like%20nickel-cadmium%20or%20nickel%20metal%20hydride.%20This%20means%20these%20can%20deliver%20large%20amounts%20of%20current%20for%20high-power%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20alternatives%20like%20solid%20state%20and%20sodium%20ion%20batteries%20are%20yet%20to%20catch%20up%2C%20lithium%20dominates%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20lithium%20ion%2C%20even%20though%20NMC%20holds%20more%20energy%20than%20LFP%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20easier%20for%20India%20to%20make%20the%20latter.%20Two%20of%20its%20inputs%20(iron%20and%20phosphate)%20are%20available%20in%20the%20country.%20Only%20lithium%20has%20to%20be%20imported.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20cost%20of%20an%20LFP%20battery%20for%20a%20bike%20will%20be%20between%20%E2%82%B918%2C000-20%2C000%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Arvind%20Bhardwaj%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CTO%20of%20Mini%20Mines%20Cleantech%20Solutions%2C%20a%20Bangalore-based%20startup%20working%20on%20lithium%20recycling.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20take%20NMC%2C%20that%20price%20doubles.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20global%20trend.%20Countries%20are%20working%20their%20way%20around%20mineral%20shortages.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%20is%20the%20major%20problem%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sen.%20Unlike%20lithium%2C%20which%20is%20found%20in%205%20or%206%20countries%2C%20cobalt%20is%20mostly%20available%20in%20the%20Congo%20where%20its%20supplies%20are%20controlled%20by%20either%20China%20or%20Belgium%20(which%20had%20colonised%20Congo).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fallout%3F%20A%20falling%20share%20of%20cobalt%20in%20rechargeable%20batteries.%20%E2%80%9CLithium%20cobalt%20oxide%20batteries%20have%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%2C%20nickel%2C%20and%20manganese%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sen.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20one%20time%2C%20these%20had%20nickel%2C%20cobalt%20and%20manganese%20in%20equal%20quantities.%20A%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20that%2033%3A33%3A33%20ratio%20changed%20to%2020%3A20%3A60.%20It%20is%20now%20becoming%2080%3A10%3A10.%20In%20some%20years%2C%20we%20might%20just%20need%20lithium%20nickel%20oxide.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20minerals%2C%20however%2C%20will%20remain%20indispensable.%20Lithium%20is%20one.%20While%20India%20is%20finding%20deposits%20within%20the%20country%2C%20it%20will%20still%20take%20years%20to%20verify%20and%20extract%20the%20mineral.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20country%20has%20ambitious%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELithium%20is%20available%20in%20two%20forms%E2%80%94as%20mineralised%20ore%20and%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fd1e00ek4ebabms.cloudfront.net%2Fproduction%2Fuploaded-files%2FLithium_redacted-5c724b64-a6a2-4863-9ccb-ddcd92b56ed8.pdf%5C%22%3Ebrine%20deposits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Australia%20has%20the%20first%2C%20known%20as%20spodumene.%20ABC%20(Argentina-Bolivia-Chile)%20have%20brine.%20Today%2C%20as%20India%20tries%20to%20secure%20lithium%20supplies%2C%20not%20only%20is%20it%20getting%20state%20agencies%20like%20KABIL%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Findl-goods%2Fsvs%2Fmetals-mining%2Findias-nmdc-explores-lithium-reserves-for-mining-in-australia%2Farticleshow%2F99608712.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3ENMDC%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20scout%20globally%20for%20reserves%2C%20it%20is%20also%20extending%20diplomatic%20support%20to%20companies%20like%20Altmin%20firming%20up%20their%20own%20supply%20arrangements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20however%2C%20is%20where%20messy%20domestic%20nuance%20enters%20the%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20Indian%20battery%20makers%20source%20components%20locally%20or%20import%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20India%20set%20up%20KABIL%20(Khanij%20Bidesh%20India%20Ltd).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20critical%20mineral%20equivalent%20of%20ONGC%20Videsh%2C%20it%20has%20to%20trawl%20the%20world%20for%20mines%E2%80%93%E2%80%93and%20grab%20as%20many%20assets%20as%20it%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedia%20reports%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining-technology.com%2Fnews%2Fkabil-camyen-lithium-extraction-projects%2F%5C%22%3Egovernment%20press%20releases%3C%2Fa%3E%20tell%20us%20the%20agency%20has%20signed%20MoUs%20to%20explore%20critical%20mineral%20reserves%20in%20Australia%E2%80%94and%20that%20it%20has%20signed%20similar%20MoUs%20with%20state%20companies%20in%20Argentina%20and%20is%20exploring%20projects%20in%20Chile.%20From%20the%20instance%20of%20Altmin%2C%20we%20also%20know%20Kabil%20wants%20to%20support%20companies%20firming%20up%20their%20own%20critical%20mineral%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20afternoon%20in%20May%2C%20CarbonCopy%20asked%20Randheer%20Singh%20about%20Altmin%20and%20Bolivia.%20Till%20June%20this%20year%2C%20Singh%20worked%20as%20director%20(e-mobility)%20and%20senior%20team%20member%20(advanced%20chemistry%20cells%20program)%20at%20Niti%20Aayog.%20He%20left%20NITI%20to%20start%20his%20own%20outfit.%20%E2%80%9CCountries%20like%20Australia%2C%20Argentina%2C%20Bolivia%20and%20Chile%20are%20taking%20control%20over%20their%20mineral%20resources%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20so%2C%20apart%20from%20KABIL%20making%20its%20own%20investments%2C%20we%20are%20encouraging%20companies%20to%20follow%20leads%20on%20their%20own.%20We%20have%20told%20them%3A%20we%20have%20connections%20with%20these%20countries.%20We%20can%20do%20the%20facilitation%20you%20need.%20The%20companies%20too%20said%20they%20want%20support.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20too%20early%20to%20say%20how%20successful%20this%20tack%20will%20be.%20As%20the%20next%20part%20of%20this%20report%20will%20show%2C%20while%20Indian%20investment%20in%20rechargeable%20battery%20manufacturing%20is%20rising%2C%20most%20firms%20have%20not%20backwards%20integrated%20to%20a%20stage%20where%20they%20need%20critical%20minerals.%20For%20instance%2C%20Tata%20wants%20to%20build%20a%2020%20GWh%20lithium%20ion%20cell%20plant.%20Reliance%E2%80%99s%20gigafactory%20for%20batteries%20will%20be%20even%20bigger%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Fril-aims-for-50-gwh-output-at-its-battery-unit-9103391.html%5C%22%3E50%20GWh%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Amara%20Raja%20batteries%20is%20building%20its%2016%20GWh%20plant%20for%20lithium%20ion%20cells.%20Exide%20is%20planning%20a%2012%20GWh%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20unclear%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Ffive-questions-india-needs-to-answer-about-its-pli-scheme%2F%5C%22%3Eif%20these%20units%20will%20source%20batteries%E2%80%99%20components%3C%2Fa%3E%20(CAM%2C%20electrolyte%2C%20anode%2C%20separator)%20locally%E2%80%94even%20making%20them%20on%20their%20own%E2%80%94or%20if%20they%20will%20buy%20those%20from%20global%20manufacturers.%20Both%20models%20exist.%20%E2%80%9CChina%E2%80%99s%20CATL%20spans%20the%20whole%20value%20chain%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sen.%20%E2%80%9COther%20companies%2C%20like%20Belgium%E2%80%99s%20Umicore%2C%20only%20straddle%20a%20particular%20rung%20in%20the%20value%20chain.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concluding%20part%20of%20this%20series%20will%20get%20into%20more%20detail%20on%20this%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20though%2C%20this%20make%20or%20import%20decision%20will%20sizably%20determine%20the%20quantum%20of%20critical%20minerals%20India%20will%20need.%20Only%20firms%20making%20cell%20components%E2%80%93%E2%80%93like%20Altmin%2C%20which%20is%20eyeing%20an%20eventual%20capacity%20of%2010%20GWh%20of%20CAM%E2%80%93%E2%80%93will%20need%20access%20to%20critical%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20question%20there%20as%20well.%20Will%20these%20firms%20want%20to%20source%20critical%20minerals%20directly%20from%20mines%3F%20Most%20of%20these%20reserves%20are%20in%20volatile%20countries%E2%80%94the%20Congo%20is%20wartorn%3B%20countries%20in%20Latin%20America%20are%20seeing%20lively%20contestations%20on%20mineral%20policies.%20It%E2%80%99s%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20engineering%20firms%20will%20not%20want%20to%20get%20into%20messy%20critical%20mineral%20mining.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20reason%2C%20several%20startups%20want%20KABIL%20to%20source%20critical%20minerals%20on%20its%20own%E2%80%94as%20opposed%20to%20expecting%20them%20to%20generate%20leads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKABIL%2C%20searching%20on%20its%20own%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKABIL%20has%20to%20scout%20for%20mines.%20Next%2C%20it%20has%20to%20bring%20processed%20minerals%20to%20India%20and%2C%20perhaps%20like%20coal%20auctions%2C%20sell%20them%20to%20bidders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20question%20here%2C%20in%20this%20time%20of%20resource%20nationalism%2C%20is%20about%20its%20attractiveness%20as%20an%20investment%20partner.%20India%20lags%20other%20countries%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20knowhow%20on%20processing%20and%20refining%20spodumene%20and%20its%20ilk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20reason%2C%20KABIL%20has%20not%20been%20very%20successful%20in%20markets%20like%20Bolivia.%20In%202021%2C%20YLB%20(again)%20began%20inviting%20international%20bids%20to%20develop%20direct%20lithium%20extraction%20technologies%20and%20extract%20lithium%20from%20its%20brine%20resources.%20None%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ylb.gob.bo%2Fresources%2Fimg%2F2Seleccion.pdf%5C%22%3E20%20companies%20on%20the%20long%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20Indian.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20it%20might%20have%20to%20take%20minority%20stakes%E2%80%94like%20ONGC%20Videsh%E2%80%94in%20producing%20mines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%2C%20however%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20more%20successful%20in%20Australia.%20The%20country%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining-technology.com%2Ffeatures%2Faustralia-lithium-production%2F%5C%22%3E5.7%20million%20tonnes%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20lithium%20reserves%2C%20second%20only%20to%20Chile.%20Not%20only%20is%20India%20a%20large%20market%2C%20Australia%20is%20also%20trying%20to%20reduce%20its%20dependence%20on%20China%E2%80%94at%20this%20time%2C%20its%20lithium%20ore%20is%20shipped%20to%20China%20for%20purification.%20Also%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20enjoy%20good%20diplomatic%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20there%20is%20the%20US-led%20Mineral%20Security%20Partnership%20(MSP).%20Not%20only%20does%20it%20aim%20to%20secure%20critical%20mineral%20supplies%20for%20its%20member%20countries%2C%20it%20also%20wants%20to%20distribute%20RE%20manufacturing%20chains%20amongst%20them%20to%20reduce%20exposure%20to%20China.%20At%20this%20time%2C%20a%20lot%20remains%20unclear%20about%20MSP%E2%80%94how%20will%20critical%20minerals%20sourced%20by%20the%20partnership%20be%20shared%20between%20members%3F%20Which%20parts%20of%20the%20manufacturing%20chain%20will%20come%20to%20India%3F%20A%20lot%20of%20ore%20processing%20is%20very%20polluting.%20And%20so%2C%20might%20India%20end%20up%20making%20a%20tradeoff%20between%20mineral%20security%20and%20environmental%20pollution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20there%20is%20domestic%20sourcing%20of%20critical%20minerals.%20This%20takes%20two%20forms.%20The%20first%20is%20domestic%20exploration.%20%E2%80%9CDespite%20having%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fifth-largest%20reserves%20of%20rare%20earth%20minerals%20in%20the%20world%2C%20India%20lags%20behind%20other%20countries%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20private%20participation%2C%20stringent%20laws%20and%20absence%20of%20technology%2C%E2%80%9D%20India%E2%80%99s%20mines%20secretary%20Vivek%20Bhardwaj%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.eepcindia.com%2Fuploads%2Fnews_update_pdfs%2Fnews_update_pdf_30062023_050019.pdf%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lithium%20found%20in%20Reasi%20fits%20in%20here.%20At%205.9%20million%20tonnes%2C%20it%20is%20putatively%20bigger%20than%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20reserves.%20It%E2%80%99s%20yet%20unclear%2C%20however%2C%20how%20much%20ore%20can%20be%20extracted%20from%20here.%20Also%20unclear%2C%20given%20the%20mountainous%20terrain%2C%20is%20its%20cost%20of%20extraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latter%20point%2C%20however%2C%20draws%20US%20shale%20to%20mind.%20Even%20if%20lithium%20from%20Reasi%20is%20expensive%2C%20it%20will%20become%20viable%20whenever%20global%20lithium%20prices%20spike%2C%20providing%20India%20with%20a%20cushion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20domestic%20sourcing%20extends%20well%20beyond%20mining.%20There%20is%20also%20the%20prospect%20of%20recycling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20India%20crack%20the%20recycling%20opportunity%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20on%20this%20report%2C%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy%3C%2Fem%3E%20met%20Arvind%20Bhardwaj%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Bangalore-based%20Mini%20Mines%20Cleantech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20startup%20is%20one%20amongst%20a%20handful%20trying%20to%20extract%20lithium%20from%20discarded%20batteries.%20As%20batteries%20age%2C%20their%20efficiency%20falls.%20The%20reasons%20vary%E2%80%94cells%20might%20leak%3B%20the%20battery%20management%20system%20might%20malfunction%3B%20lithium%20ions%20might%20adhere%20poorly%20to%20ageing%20electrodes%3B%20one%20could%20go%20on.%20At%20this%20stage%2C%20batteries%20sent%20for%20recycling%20are%20shredded%2C%20their%20constituent%20cells%20crushed.%20After%20removing%20the%20more%20easily%20isolated%20components%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20plastic%20and%20Iron%20covering%20is%20removed%20first.%20And%20then%2C%20the%20aluminium%20and%20then%20copper%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bhardwaj.%20What%20is%20left%20is%20a%20black%20powder%20called%20Black%20Mass.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20chemistry%20of%20the%20battery%E2%80%94graphite%2C%20lithium%2C%20iron%2C%20phosphate%3B%20or%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%2C%20Nickel%2C%20and%20manganese%3B%20or%20lithium%20and%20titanium%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20type%20of%20cell%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20things%20get%20interesting.%20If%20lithium%20refining%20is%20about%20breaking%20spodumene%2C%20an%20undifferentiated%20clump%20of%20minerals%2C%20into%20its%20constituent%20elements%2C%20recycling%20has%20a%20similar%20task%20on%20its%20hand.%20Till%20recently%2C%20firms%20recycling%20rechargeable%20batteries%20stripped%20what%20they%20could%20extract%20and%20exported%20the%20black%20mass%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flithiumionbattery.org%2Findustry-updates%2Fnews%2Fthe-cobalt-crunch-for-electric-cars-could-be-solved-in-suburbia%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20like%20Umicore%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20changing%20now.%20Startups%20like%20Mini%20Mines%20and%20Meta%20Stable%20are%20trying%20to%20extract%20critical%20minerals%20themselves.%20One%20tonne%20of%20crushed%20battery%20will%20yield%2C%20he%20told%20CarbonCopy%2C%2030-40%20kilos%20of%20lithium%20carbonate.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20be%20able%20to%20extract%20about%2096%25%20of%20lithium%20from%20the%20battery%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20That%20is%20just%20the%20start.%20Ore%20and%20brine%20contain%20no%20more%20than%200.6%25%20lithium%2C%20at%20best.%20In%20contrast%2C%20as%20Bhardwaj%20said%2C%20the%20concentration%20of%20lithium%20(or%20any%20other%20critical%20mineral)%20in%20a%20battery%20runs%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20reason%2C%20he%20added%2C%20recycled%20lithium%20will%20be%20cheaper.%20This%20claim%20was%20reiterated%20by%20Larry%20Reaugh%2C%20the%20president%20of%20American%20Manganese%2C%20a%20Vancouver-based%20company%20working%20on%20rechargeable%20battery%20recycling.%20His%20firm%20can%20extract%20metals%20at%2030%20cents%20a%20pound%2C%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flithiumionbattery.org%2Findustry-updates%2Fnews%2Fthe-cobalt-crunch-for-electric-cars-could-be-solved-in-suburbia%5C%22%3Ean%20industry%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20put%20that%20in%20context%2C%20the%20price%20of%20cobalt%20stood%20at%20%2441%20by%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20reason%2C%20if%20the%20recycling%20ecosystem%20takes%20off%2C%20India%20might%20need%20to%20import%20lithium%20only%20for%20new%20demand%E2%80%94not%20replacement%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20catch%20here%3A%20the%20world%20is%20seeing%20a%20race%20in%20recycling%20technology%20as%20well.%20And%2C%20as%20CarbonCopy%20had%20found%20while%20reporting%20on%20PLI%2C%20India%20is%20doling%20out%20manufacturing%20subsidies%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Ffive-questions-india-needs-to-answer-about-its-pli-scheme%2F%5C%22%3Enot%20investing%20in%20fundamental%20R%26amp%3BD%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20supply%20side%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPut%20it%20all%20together%20and%20it%20becomes%20clear%20that%20India%20has%20multiple%20pathways%20for%20securing%20critical%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20the%20country%20paring%20its%20requirements%20of%20hard-to-find%20minerals%2C%20it%20is%20extending%20diplomatic%20support%20to%20companies%20while%20getting%20KABIL%20and%20NMDC%20to%20scout%20for%20mineral%20reserves%20globally.%20It%20has%20also%20entered%20the%20Mineral%20Security%20Partnership%20and%20is%20prospecting%20domestically.%20Apart%20from%20these%2C%20there%20is%20the%20prospect%20of%20recycling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20these%20measures%20aren%E2%80%99t%20enough%20to%20insulate%20the%20country%20from%20geopolitical%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%2C%20Chinese%20firms%20dominate%20the%20lower%20reaches%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20two-wheeler%20and%20three-wheeler%20EV%20markets.%20Firms%20like%20BYD%20and%20MG%20have%20entered%20the%20four-wheeler%20market%20as%20well.%20If%20these%20firms%20reprise%20China%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20solar%20panels%20in%20the%20EV%20market%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-06-08%2Fmodi-s-make-in-india-goal-relies-on-china-factories-for-supplies%3Fsref%3DzsRxy7Ix%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3Eor%20if%20Indian%20firms%20continue%20sourcing%20components%20from%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20dependence%20on%20Chinese%20supply%20chains%20will%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20if%20other%20countries%20make%20rapid%20inroads%20into%20India%E2%80%99s%20energy%20storage%20market%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20dependence%20on%20them%20will%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20vulnerability%20runs%20deeper%20than%20just%20critical%20mineral%20supplies.%20To%20meaningfully%20insulate%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20a